# Platform Engineering Rules

## Terraform / HCL

- All resources must include the standard tag block: `Platform`, `Environment`, `Team`, `ManagedBy`, `CostCenter`
- Use explicit version constraints for providers and modules (`~>` patch-level pinning)
- All variables must have a `description` and `type`
- Prefer `data` sources over hardcoded IDs
- No hardcoded credentials, regions, or account IDs — use variables

## Kubernetes Manifests

- Always set `resources.requests` and `resources.limits`
- Required labels: `app`, `version`, `team`, `managed-by`
- Set `securityContext.readOnlyRootFilesystem: true` by default
- Never use `privileged: true` without an inline comment explaining why
- `hostNetwork: true` and `hostPID: true` are forbidden in platform resources

## CI/CD Pipelines (GitHub Actions / GitLab CI)

- Use OIDC (`id-token: write`) for cloud authentication — no service account keys
- Pin action versions to full commit SHA, not floating tags
- Security scanning must precede any deploy step
- Production jobs must use an `environment:` with required reviewers
- Never log secrets — use `::add-mask::` or equivalent

## General

- No inline secrets or credentials anywhere in the codebase
- Comments explain *why*, not *what*
- When in doubt, be more explicit — platform code is read more than it is written
